<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1106,1638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1395,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sinclair, B. J." box="[272,492,1394,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="197 - 228" refId="ref11855" refString="Sinclair, B. J. (2010) Revision and phylogenetic systematics of the Neotropical Ceratomerinae (Insecta: Diptera: Empidoidea: Brachystomatidae). Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny, 68 (2), 197 - 228." type="journal article" year="2010">Sinclair (2010: 205)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<specimenCount box="[555,733,1395,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of this species from “Pata de Gallina”, collected “ 
<date box="[1272,1421,1394,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" value="1993-01-10" valueMax="1993-01-25" valueMin="1993-01-10">10-25.i.1993</date>
”, locating this point in 
<collectingRegion box="[394,583,1431,1457]" country="Chile" name="Atacama" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Atacama Region</collectingRegion>
in the desert area of 
<collectingCountry box="[826,889,1431,1457]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Chile</collectingCountry>
, a record we consider as erroneous, as there are some localities with this name at different latitudes in 
<collectingCountry box="[784,848,1467,1493]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Chile</collectingCountry>
. To be accurate we need to consider the collection data given for 
<specimenCount box="[314,438,1503,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sinclair" authorityYear="2010" box="[475,665,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Ceratomerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraconnexus">
<emphasis box="[475,665,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">C. paraconnexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sinclair, B. J." box="[707,936,1503,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="197 - 228" refId="ref11855" refString="Sinclair, B. J. (2010) Revision and phylogenetic systematics of the Neotropical Ceratomerinae (Insecta: Diptera: Empidoidea: Brachystomatidae). Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny, 68 (2), 197 - 228." type="journal article" year="2010">Sinclair (2010: 214)</bibRefCitation>
, collected at “S. Concepcion, Laraquete, 
<date pageId="3" pageNumber="152" value="1993-01-10" valueMax="1993-01-25" valueMin="1993-01-10">10- 25.i.1993</date>
, P. Salinas”; the identical collection date leads us to associate the collection locality of Pata de Gallina to 
<collectingRegion box="[179,370,1575,1601]" country="Chile" name="Araucania" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Arauco Province</collectingRegion>
(exactly S of Contulmo), for its vicinity to Laraquete, more than in homonymous localities in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,227,1611,1637]" country="Chile" name="Biobio" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Biobío</collectingRegion>
(SW Los Angeles) or Concepción (
<quantity box="[628,685,1611,1637]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" unit="km" value="6.0">6 km</quantity>
S Concepcion, urban area) provinces.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
